And they discovered a poem she wrote, praising the ideology of Al Qaeda mastermind Osama Bin Laden, who was killed in Pakistan by US troops in May 2011.

Typed clumsily after his death, Lewthwaite proclaims her love for the terrorist chief.

She wrote: ‘Oh Sheik Osama my father, my brother / My love for you is like no other / Oh Sheik Osama now that you are gone / The Muslims must wake up they must be strong.’

